from shapely.geometry import Point

#Encontrando entre qu puerto y aeropuerta corresponde la menor distancia
distance_matrix = seaports_australia_3112.set_index('portName').geometry.apply(
    lambda g: largeAirports.set_index('name').geometry.distance(g) / 1000
).sort_index(axis=0).sort_index(axis=1)

#Hallando la fila y columna con el menor valor
min_row, min_col = distance_matrix.stack().idxmin()

print(f"The minimum distance is at row '{min_row}' and column '{min_col}'")

# Graficamos Hull Murray con su aeropuerto ms cerca y lejano. Lo mismo para Hull Darling

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

# ... (Your existing code) ...


def plot_closest_farthest_airports(hull_system, distance_matrix):
    """Plots the closest and farthest airports to a given river system hull."""

    # Find the closest and farthest airports to the hull
    closest_airport = distance_matrix.loc[hull_system].idxmin()
    farthest_airport = distance_matrix.loc[hull_system].idxmax()
    closest_distance = distance_matrix.loc[hull_system].min()
    farthest_distance = distance_matrix.loc[hull_system].max()

    # Get the geometries for the closest and farthest airports
    closest_airport_geometry = largeAirports[largeAirports['name'] == closest_airport].geometry.iloc[0]
    farthest_airport_geometry = largeAirports[largeAirports['name'] == farthest_airport].geometry.iloc[0]

    # Plot the base map (Australia)
    base = australia_3112.plot(color='lightgray', edgecolor='gray')

    # Plot the hull
    systems_hulls[systems_hulls['system'] == hull_system].plot(ax=base, color='orange', edgecolor='black', alpha=0.5, label=f'{hull_system} Hull')

    # Plot the closest and farthest airports
    plt.plot(closest_airport_geometry.x, closest_airport_geometry.y, 'go', label=f'Closest Airport: {closest_airport} ({closest_distance:.2f} km)')
    plt.plot(farthest_airport_geometry.x, farthest_airport_geometry.y, 'ro', label=f'Farthest Airport: {farthest_airport} ({farthest_distance:.2f} km)')

    # Add labels and title
    plt.xlabel("Longitude")
    plt.ylabel("Latitude")
    plt.title(f"Closest and Farthest Airports to {hull_system} River System Hull")
    plt.legend()

    plt.show()


# Example usage for the Murray-Darling systems
plot_closest_farthest_airports('Murray', distanceMatrixKM_sysHull_air)
plot_closest_farthest_airports('Darling', distanceMatrixKM_sysHull_air)
